# ─── Two-key (siloed) model ──────────────────────────────────────────
# The Ninja API and the TTMA Voice API are separate services. The demo
# holds ONE key per silo and never lets a credential cross APIs. Mint each
# in its own dashboard:
#
# NINJA_API_KEY → api.moltbot.ninja   (mint at https://app.moltbot.ninja → API Keys)
#   Scopes (Ninja silo):
#     - deployments:read
#     - agents:write
#     - blueprints:read
#     - blueprints:deploy
#     - voice:install     (optional — dispatch the voice gateway onto the agent)
#     - voice:uninstall   (optional — DELETE flow; demo has no UI for it yet)
#     - files:write       (optional — the AI seeding step rewrites SOUL.md
#                          (the agent persona) after the deploy completes.
#                          Without it that step is skipped and the blueprint's
#                          templated SOUL.md stands.)
#   Scope it to the FLEET deployment you deploy onto (e.g. Quan).
NINJA_API_KEY=mbn_live_REPLACE_ME

# TTMA_API_KEY → api.talktomyagent.io  (mint in the TTMA portal → API Keys)
#   Scopes (TTMA silo) — only needed for the voice + Wix flow:
#     - voice:read              (list voice deployments)
#     - voice:apps              (install the Wix Bookings app)
#     - voice:install-bundles   (mint install bundles)
#   Scope it to the VOICE deployment you install from (e.g. Billy).
#   Leave blank to run the Ninja-only blueprint flow without voice.
TTMA_API_KEY=mbn_live_REPLACE_ME

# ─── Legacy single-key fallback (optional) ───────────────────────────
# If NINJA_API_KEY / TTMA_API_KEY above are unset, both silos fall back to
# this one key. Only works if the key carries BOTH silos' scopes (a
# cross-API key). Prefer the two-key model above.
# MBN_API_KEY=mbn_live_REPLACE_ME

# ─── API bases ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Ninja public REST API. Production: https://api.moltbot.ninja
# Local emulator (Firebase Functions): http://localhost:5001/<project>/us-central1/api
MBN_API_BASE=https://api.moltbot.ninja

# TTMA voice-api base. Production: https://api.talktomyagent.io
TTMA_API_BASE=https://api.talktomyagent.io

# ─── AI file seeding (optional) ──────────────────────────────────────
# After the blueprint deploy completes, the demo can use Anthropic to read
# the introspected site and rewrite SOUL.md (the agent persona) as a
# business-tailored phone receptionist, so it sounds like a human employee
# of that business instead of generic boilerplate. The booking flow and the
# site's service/staff data are already seeded by the blueprint (in the
# voice playbook) — the demo deliberately does NOT touch that tuned file.
#
# This is the DEMO's job, not the Ninja API's — the API only exposes the
# files PUT. Leave ANTHROPIC_API_KEY blank to skip seeding entirely; the
# blueprint's templated SOUL.md remains (a working baseline). Requires the
# NINJA_API_KEY to additionally carry the `files:write` scope (see above).
#
# The Anthropic key talks ONLY to api.anthropic.com — it never crosses into
# the Ninja or TTMA silos.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-REPLACE_ME
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
